<%- include('partials/header') %>

    <section class="hero">
        <div class="hero-badge">⚠️ Intentionally Vulnerable</div>
        <h1>Welcome to <span class="gradient-text">BreachMe</span></h1>
        <p>
            A deliberately insecure web application designed for learning and practicing
            web security testing. Explore, exploit, and understand common vulnerabilities.
        </p>
    </section>

    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header">
            <h2>🎯 Vulnerability Challenges</h2>
            <p>Each page contains a real, exploitable vulnerability. Can you find and exploit them all?</p>
        </div>

        <div class="vuln-grid">
            <div class="card vuln-card sql">
                <div class="vuln-tag tag-critical">🔴 Critical</div>
                <h3>SQL Injection</h3>
                <p>
                    <strong>What is it?</strong> When a website puts your input directly into a database
                    query without checking it. You can trick it into running your own commands.
                </p>
                <p><strong>Where:</strong> Login page — bypass authentication without a password.</p>
                <a href="/login" class="vuln-link">Try it →</a>
            </div>

            <div class="card vuln-card xss">
                <div class="vuln-tag tag-critical">🔴 Critical</div>
                <h3>Stored XSS</h3>
                <p>
                    <strong>What is it?</strong> When a website saves your input and displays it to others
                    without cleaning it. You can inject JavaScript that runs in everyone's browser.
                </p>
                <p><strong>Where:</strong> Guestbook — inject a script that executes for every visitor.</p>
                <a href="/guestbook" class="vuln-link">Try it →</a>
            </div>

            <div class="card vuln-card cmd">
                <div class="vuln-tag tag-critical">🔴 Critical</div>
                <h3>Command Injection</h3>
                <p>
                    <strong>What is it?</strong> When a website runs system commands with your input.
                    You can sneak in extra commands on the server's operating system.
                </p>
                <p><strong>Where:</strong> Network Tools page — execute arbitrary OS commands.</p>
                <a href="/tools" class="vuln-link">Try it →</a>
            </div>

            <div class="card vuln-card idor">
                <div class="vuln-tag tag-high">🟡 High</div>
                <h3>IDOR (Insecure Direct Object Ref)</h3>
                <p>
                    <strong>What is it?</strong> When a website lets you access other people's data just
                    by changing a number in the URL. No authorization check.
                </p>
                <p><strong>Where:</strong> Profile page — view others' private data by changing the ID.</p>
                <% if (user) { %>
                <a href="/profile/<%= user.id %>" class="vuln-link">Try it →</a>
                <% } else { %>
                <a href="/login" class="vuln-link">Login first →</a>
                <% } %>
            </div>

            <div class="card vuln-card csrf">
                <div class="vuln-tag tag-high">🟡 High</div>
                <h3>CSRF (Cross-Site Request Forgery)</h3>
                <p>
                    <strong>What is it?</strong> When a website doesn't verify requests came from its own
                    page. An attacker can trick your browser into making unintended requests.
                </p>
                <p><strong>Where:</strong> Change Password page — no CSRF token protection.</p>
                <% if (user) { %>
                <a href="/change-password" class="vuln-link">Try it →</a>
                <% } else { %>
                <a href="/login" class="vuln-link">Login first →</a>
                <% } %>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card mt-4" style="text-align: center;">
            <h3>🕵️ Bonus: Hidden API Endpoint</h3>
            <p class="text-muted mt-1">
                There's also a hidden API that leaks sensitive data. Can you find it?<br>
                <em>Hint: Try exploring <code>/api/</code> endpoints...</em>
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card mt-2" style="text-align: center;">
            <h3>📚 Default Test Accounts</h3>
            <p class="text-muted mt-1" style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.8rem;">
                admin / admin123 &nbsp;·&nbsp; john / password1 &nbsp;·&nbsp; alice / letmein &nbsp;·&nbsp; bob / qwerty
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <%- include('partials/footer') %>